info.title: PlayFab Multiplayer API
info.description: API methods for managing multiplayer servers.

post.description: Creates a multiplayer server build with a custom container.
post.x-requestDetails: Creates a multiplayer server build with a custom container and returns information about the build creation request.

post.description: Creates a multiplayer server build with a managed container.
post.x-requestDetails: Creates a multiplayer server build with a managed container and returns information about the build creation request.

post.description: Creates a remote user to log on to a VM for a multiplayer server build.
post.x-requestDetails: Creates a remote user to log on to a VM for a multiplayer server build in a specific region. Returns user credential information necessary to log on.

post.description: Deletes a multiplayer server game asset for a title.
post.x-requestDetails: Deletes a multiplayer server game asset for a title.

post.description: Deletes a multiplayer server build.
post.x-requestDetails: Deletes a multiplayer server build.

post.description: Deletes a multiplayer server game certificate.
post.x-requestDetails: Deletes a multiplayer server game certificate.

post.description: Deletes a remote user to log on to a VM for a multiplayer server build.
post.x-requestDetails: Deletes a remote user to log on to a VM for a multiplayer server build in a specific region. Returns user credential information necessary to log on.

post.description: Enables the multiplayer server feature for a title.
post.x-requestDetails: Enables the multiplayer server feature for a title and returns the enabled status. The enabled status can be Initializing, Enabled, and Disabled. It can up to 20 minutes or more for the title to be enabled for the feature. On average, it can take up to 20 minutes for the title to be enabled for the feature.

post.description: Gets the URL to upload assets to.
post.x-requestDetails: Gets the URL to upload assets to.

post.description: Gets a multiplayer server build.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns the details about a multiplayer server build.

post.description: Gets the credentials to the container registry.
post.x-requestDetails: Gets credentials to the container registry where game developers can upload custom container images to before creating a new build.

post.description: Gets multiplayer server session details for a build.
post.x-requestDetails: Gets multiplayer server session details for a build in a specific region.

post.description: Gets a remote login endpoint to a VM that is hosting a multiplayer server build.
post.x-requestDetails: Gets a remote login endpoint to a VM that is hosting a multiplayer server build in a specific region.

post.description: Gets the status of whether a title is enabled for the multiplayer server feature.
post.x-requestDetails: Gets the status of whether a title is enabled for the multiplayer server feature. The enabled status can be Initializing, Enabled, and Disabled.

post.description: Lists archived multiplayer server sessions for a build.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of archived multiplayer servers for a build in a specific region.

post.description: Lists multiplayer server game assets for a title.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of multiplayer server game asset summaries for a title.

post.description: Lists summarized details of all multiplayer server builds for a title.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of summarized details of all multiplayer server builds for a title.

post.description: Lists multiplayer server game certificates for a title.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of multiplayer server game certificates for a title.

post.description: Lists custom container images for a title.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of the container images that have been uploaded to the container registry for a title.

post.description: Lists the tags for a custom container image.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of the tags for a particular container image that exists in the container registry for a title.

post.description: Lists multiplayer server sessions for a build.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of multiplayer servers for a build in a specific region.

post.description: Lists quality of service servers.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of quality of service servers.

post.description: Lists virtual machines for a title.
post.x-requestDetails: Returns a list of virtual machines for a title.

post.description: Request a multiplayer server session. Accepts tokens for title and if game client accesss is enabled, allows game client to request a server with player entity token.
post.x-requestDetails: Requests a multiplayer server session from a particular build in any of the given preferred regions.

post.description: Rolls over the credentials to the container registry.
post.x-requestDetails: Gets new credentials to the container registry where game developers can upload custom container images to before creating a new build.

post.description: Shuts down a multiplayer server session.
post.x-requestDetails: Executes the shutdown callback from the GSDK and terminates the multiplayer server session. The callback in the GSDK will allow for graceful shutdown with a 15 minute timeoutIf graceful shutdown has not been completed before 15 minutes have elapsed, the multiplayer server session will be forcefully terminated on it's own.

post.description: Updates a multiplayer server build's regions.
post.x-requestDetails: Updates a multiplayer server build's regions.

post.description: Uploads a multiplayer server game certificate.
post.x-requestDetails: Uploads a multiplayer server game certificate.
